description.0: It's a romantic love square between Mantis, Vision, Scarlet Witch and the Swordsman! Mantis has the hots for Vision. Scarlet Witch wants her gone. Swordsman feels he isn't good enough for Mantis. The Vision questions which lady he truly loves. Meanwhile, Black Panther is tricked into a trap by a racist ambassador, but will his teammates be too unfocused by their love affairs to aid their teammate in his time of need?
description.1: Steve Rogers has had enough! The Star-Spangled Soldier renounces his Captain America identity... for good!
description.7: Morbius returns from The Land Within only to wake up on a strange planet… and with a gnawing hunger.
description.14: Nebulon is the man behind the plan of the Squadron Sinister and it's the villains united versus the Defenders. Plus, a new member joins the Defenders team.
description.16: The fight against Black Spectre continues as Daredevil faces their new ally, The Silver Samurai!
description.17: Hulk believes he is in Washington D.C., but actually finds himself on Counter-Earth! Will Hulk be able to survive on a parallel planet so different from his own?
description.18: A new herald of Galactus rises! Borne of flames comes...Firelord!
description.19: Dracula's battles against his fellow vampires continues! His opponent this time - GORNA, Lord of the Living Lightning!
description.20: When it rains, it pours! The disheartened FF return to the Baxter Building sans Sue Storm, who has vowed to stay with Namor forever. But waiting for them is the Frightful Four, ready for a Battle Royale!
description.26: A mega-sized issue featuring som of Marvel's most menacing monsters! With a special spotlight on Werewolf by Night, and introducing the fury of TIGRA!
description.27: Valkyrie is shown the startling pasts of her Defender teammates!
description.30: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 5: The Panther brings the fight to King Cadaver and Macabre at Cadaver's lair beneath the cemetery. Contains only "King Cadaver Is Dead and Living In Wakanda" story.
description.34: The first appearance of Tarantula! Peter takes a day of leisure to go on a cruise with MJ, Flash, and Liz Allan. While onboard, a masked mercenary attacks! Plus, Harry Osborn discovers Peter's greatest secret!
description.35: The Avengers band together to face the cosmic invasion force of the Mad Titan Thanos! Can Earth's Mightiest Heroes defend the planet from this dire threat?
description.36: Cap and the Falcon manage to defeat the Secret Empire, but can they survive the likes of the deadiest Man-Menace of all? Find out in this action-packed issue!
description.37: This is it, True Believers! Captain Marvel and the Avengers combat the terror of the now god-like Thanos!
description.40: Ka-Zar and Bobbi Morse vs. the Man-God!
description.45: Following a fight, Daredevil unveils the truth behind the Black Spectre gang and affirms the theory that its members are all women with mysterious facial tattoos. But where does the mutant Mandrill factor in?
description.46: Dave Barnett presents a violent ultimatum to Johnny Blaze in order to stop the Zodiac cartel.
description.47: It's one man against two when Iron Man takes on the Unicorn and the mutant called Sunfire! Plus: Don't dare miss the shocking secret of Iron Man's new mask! It's action! It's excitement! It's mystery! All in the Marvel way!
description.48: The Destroyer walks again! But which villain has re-animated this destructive hunk of metal? Krista faces grave injuries that only Donald Blake can fix.
description.49: Clash of the vampires! Dracula is forced into a duel to the death with Lucas Brand, vampire thrall of Doctor Sun!
description.50: This spooky edition of Vampire Tales features a story of Morbius versus your Friendly Neighborhood SPIDER-MAN!
description.51: Mister Fantastic is served with divorce papers! Johnny and Ben discover that Sue and Franklin are missing in their effort to save the marriage of Reed and Sue- and that she is actually the hostage of Namor!
description.52: Following his destruction of the Inhumans' home, Hulk is launched into the vastness of space. Not realizing he is onboard a space shuttle, Hulk smashes "free", and nearly pilots himself, and the crew, into the sun!
description.53: Hawkeye and Spider-Man find themselves at odds but that may just the opening these mysterious metal men need to destroy the heroes!
description.54: John Jameson fears the worst when he starts experiencing headaches after being cured of the Moon-Stone's possession Featuring the return of two of Spider-Man's greatest foes; Morbius the Living Vampire, and Man-Wolf!
description.57: Fin Fang Foom is controlled by Dr. Vault!
description.59: Giving Dracula diplomatic immunity seems like a dangerous thing...but it would go a long way towards keeping cops from hunting him down whenever he hunts in London!
description.64: Ned Leeds and Spider-Man are sickened by Molten Man's irradiated bursts. MJ finds out about Molten Man's past through her friend, Liz Allan. Who was Mark Raxton before he was a villain? And what is he seeking from Spider-Man?
description.65: The Avengers must travel to Vietnam to stop the Swordsman from committing murder. And who is the Swordsman's target? None other than Monsieur Khruul and his creature, Star Stalker! Plus, more of Mantis' mysterious past revealed!
description.66: Can Captain America and the Falcon survive their showdown with the Secret Empire?
description.67: The demonic Balkatar has Morbius cornered… but refuses to make a kill. King Gerark welcomes Morbius to his kingdom.
description.69: Daredevil goes head-to-head with Black Spectre! Mister Fantastic makes an appearance!
description.70: Nighthawk warns the Defenders of the return of the Squadron Sinister, which means only one thing - super-team showdown!
description.72: As Black Spectre continues their streak of vandalism, the organization tries to (unsuccessfully) recruit Daredevil and Black Widow.
description.74: Bruce Banner is hurled to Attilan where he is greeted by the Inhumans. But when provoked into becoming the Hulk, the Inhumans realize why some things are better left on Earth!
description.75: Thor's final battle with Pluto! But will Krista be a casualty in this clash of the gods? Donald Blake may have to make an untimely appearance...
description.76: Trapped in the Alps! Dracula is stranded with no way to survive - but if Doctor Sun has his way, the vampire won't live long enough to lament his plight!
description.77: The Human Torch and Medusa have crash-landed in the Himalayas, and find themselves helpless under a layer of ice made by the Climate Cannon! Throughout this adventure, Johnny and Medusa are aided by some icy friends and- The Thing?
description.81: Stunned by a spell from Xandu, Spider-Man steals the Crystal of Kadavarus in order to bring back the evil mage's love from a coma. Guest-starring Doctor Strange!
description.86: Maa-gor recruits El Tigre to help him take down Ka-Zar. S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent Bobbi Morse arrives in the nick of time!
description.88: PANTHER'S RAGE PART 4: T'Challa fights another one of Killmonger's cronies: Baron Macabre, a man who uses corpses as servants! Contains only "But Now the Spears Are Broken" story.
description.91: Trouble arises for both Peter Parker and Ned Leeds, as the Molten Man continues his reign of terror! With Molten Man's powers strengthened, will Spider-Man be able to overcome one of his greatest opponents yet? Plus, Ned finds himself in grave danger after being exposed to heavy radiation.
description.92: Mantis' origin issue! The newest and most mysterious member of the Avengers reveals her past; including her ties to the Zodiac's Libra!
description.93: Make way for the Marvel Age of Comics! Captain America, the Falcon, and the X-Men in deadly combat with the Nick Fury and his hell-raising Agents of Shield!
description.94: Mar-Vell against demonic forces! Rick Jones confronts Thanos! Plus: the origins of Drax and Moondragon are revealed!
description.98: Stegron takes his destruction tour on the road to NYC and Spidey will need the help of Black Panther to tackle the man-dinosaur!

2.text: AN ACTION PACKED KUNG FU TALE! Lin Sun, Abe Brown and Robert Diamond are after the notorious Lo Chin.

3.text: Power Man finds himself on a very strange mission, attempting to steal heroin for Cottonmouth.

4.text: Wounded and stalked by Fu Manchu's assassins Jekin and Dahar, Shang-Chi makes his way through the Florida swamps. Meanwhile, Sir Denis partners up with Black Jack Tarr to try and put an end to Fu Manchu!

8.text: Will La Hacienda house the Fountain of Youth? Schist and Hargood certainly think so! Man-Thing must defend Lorena from an opportunistic plot. The Man-Thing’s muck is siphoned off, and the creature slowly becomes more man than thing. Could this be the return of Ted Sallis?

9.text: The indomitable Glob is born from the ill-fated Joseph Timms! Science and nature collide with grotesque consequences.

10.text: Lissa is in peril once again! This time Jack must save his sister from Baron Thunder and Ma Mayhem!

12.text: Behold! The birth of the cyborg known as Deathlok! Military strategist Col. Luther Manning loses his humanity in a post-apocalyptic science experiment. Now, trapped in an amalgam of flesh and circuitry, Deathlok lives between life and death, man and robot.

14.text: Nebulon is the man behind the plan of the Squadron Sinister and it's the villains united versus the Defenders. Plus, a new member joins the Defenders team.

15.text: Iron Fist gets the New York treatment when he’s attacked by street thugs upon arrival from K’un-Lun. Plus, Fist discovers there’s a bounty on his head! Who is the mercenary Scythe, and who hired him to eliminate Iron Fist?

23.text: Piranha has the antidote! With time running out for the people of Atlantis, Namor will have to fight harder than ever before to save them!

24.text: Iceman butts heads with the Human Torch when someone sets him up to take the fall for a jewelry store robbery.

25.text: Daimon Hellstrom's next foe comes from an unexpected place - his own magic!?

28.text: Spider-Man is caught between a rock and a hard place when Dracula, Lord of Vampires, becomes invested in the Maggia's dealings!

29.text: John Jameson howls, claws and snarls his way into a solo adventure! Think you know Spider-Man’s werewolf menace? The Man-Wolf hunts at night. Beware!

30.text: Contains only "King Cadaver Is Dead and Living In Wakanda" story. PANTHER’S RAGE PART 5: The Panther brings the fight to King Cadaver and Macabre at Cadaver’s lair beneath the cemetery.

33.text: Who is Skar, and what is his purpose in destroying Killraven? In Indianapolis, the Freemen rise up against a new agent of the Martians, this time waging war at the famed Motor Speedway!

38.text: Bucking his role as lackey, Ivan takes command by saving the Monster from a grotesque end. Vincent Frankenstein may lose it all, including his beloved Lenore. A weird science project spells disaster for the last Frankenstein!

39.text: F.A. Schist may have abandoned his plan to build an airport, but now he’s dead set on a new goal- to find the Fountain of Youth! What begins as fanciful imagination may end in death. But for who?

40.text: Ka-Zar and Bobbi Morse vs. the Man-God!

41.text: It’s a Hollywood horror battle when werewolves Jack and Richard fight two vampires on a film set!

43.text: Behold, True Believers! Doc Strange casts a new spell in his second ongoing series. Silver Dagger has infiltrated the Sanctum Sanctorum…and claims the Sorcerer Supreme is actually a demon in disguise!

56.text: The life of Darrel the Clown reenacted! In an effort to put his spirit to rest, members of Garvey’s circus play out the clown’s life from childhood to death. The strange and twisted saga culminates in final judgment from The Critics.

57.text: Fin Fang Foom is controlled by Dr. Vault!

58.text: Jack discovers that his stand-offish neighbor Raymond Coker also possesses powerful werewolf powers!

60.text: What happens when your father becomes your worst enemy? IT’S FATHER VS. SON IN THE ORIGIN OF SHANG-CHI! Troubled by his past, Shang-Chi in the present is forced to fight a band of fighters including his mad father. When next they meet, it will be as implacable enemies…

61.text: Special delivery for Power Man! Luke is gifted with two poisonous snakes in a box…!

62.text: Will Shang-Chi evade his father's capture long enough to destroy a shipment of sedative-laced gasoline?

69.text: Daredevil goes head-to-head with Black Spectre! Mister Fantastic makes an appearance!

70.text: Nighthawk warns the Defenders of the return of the Squadron Sinister, which means only one thing - super-team showdown!

73.text: Why is the HULK in New York? He wonders this as he falls asleep in an alley somewhere -- only to wake up and bump into Thing of the Fantastic Four!

80.text: Namor's search for a cure to the affliction Atlantis suffers continues! But to get a key ingredient, he'll have to brave the mysterious ruins of a WWII submarine - and face down Piranha and the Men-Fish!

82.text: Round 2 at Gate University! Daimon is called back to the school to square off against a Satanic Cult, but the dark cabal has a trick up their sleeve that might be too much for even Daimon to handle...

83.text: 2019 A.D., the last year of man!? Killraven and the Freemen do battle against the High Overlord at the Lincoln Memorial!

84.text: Vincent Frankenstein claims to be the last surviving member of his all but ruined family. Together, with hunchbacked assistant Ivan, Vincent swears to right the wrongs of his predecessors. Will the Monster learn of Vincent’s true intentions?

85.text: It’s no laughing matter when a clown takes his life on the banks of the Citrusville swamps. A circus of consequences ensues, as Ruth and Richard find themselves center ring when solving the mystery of the clown’s disappearance. Man-Thing is deeply misunderstood. The spirit of Darrel the Clown rises.

86.text: Maa-gor recruits El Tigre to help him take down Ka-Zar. S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent Bobbi Morse arrives in the nick of time!

87.text: Jack and Topaz arrive in California where the Committee has long awaited their return…

88.text: Contains only "But Now the Spears Are Broken" story. PANTHER’S RAGE PART 4: T’Challa fights another one of Killmonger’s cronies: Baron Macabre, a man who uses corpses as servants!

99.text: Brother Voodoo consorts with the clairvoyant Mama Limbo to uncover the whereabouts of Loralee Tate.
